# Portfolio Tab Documentation Update Protocol

**Development Log (portfolio-planning.md, always last section)**:
- Format: `[Step/Stage] ([Name]) – [User Command] – [Comprehensive Details]: [files examined with line counts], [changes made with specific line numbers], [what was tested with results], [decisions made with scores/metrics]. Result: [Stage] COMPLETE with [deliverables], [next status].`
- Include: Exact line numbers for all changes, quantifiable metrics (line counts, scores, percentages), file names with total lines, test results with exit codes/outcomes, technical specifics (not summaries)
- Principle: Write assuming zero context - new chat must understand what happened from this entry alone
- Never add content below development log

**Step Status Updates (portfolio-planning.md)**:
- Mark `**Status**: ✅ COMPLETE` when all stages finished
- Update `**Result**` and `**Output**` fields to show concrete achievements (add ✅)
- Keep Prerequisites/Purpose/Logic Doc Reference/Tech-Ref Lines unchanged

**Phase Completion**:
- Update phase header: `## PHASE X: [NAME] ✅ COMPLETE`
- Add `**Status**: ✅ ALL STEPS COMPLETE (list steps)`
- Add `**Deliverables**:` section with ✅ checkmarks
- Update tech-ref.md: Mark phase complete in Step Reference Guide and Critical Requirements Checklist

**Development Information Section (portfolio-planning.md after line 878)**:
- Add analysis/planning details with tables (comparison matrices, complexity scores, decision matrices)
- Include complete code examples (not snippets), exact line references, metrics
- Use subsections with clear headers for each stage's findings

**Key Principles**:
- Reference exact line numbers for all source material
- Include quantifiable data (line counts, percentages, scores, time estimates)
- Assume reader has no prior context (comprehensive over concise)
- Never use abbreviations in development log
- Document test results explicitly (✅/❌, exit codes, what was verified)